Euro/USD Example

2024-09-18

Load Packages

Import Euro/USD data

This data is given to us in the form of: Date (day, month, year), Time (5-minute time intervals), Euro/USD bid price, Euro/USD ask price.

The data is already clean and well-formatted in date, time form; however, it gives us the Euro/USD bid and ask prices, not returns, therefore we must calculate Returns from this data.

exchange <- read.csv("EuroUSD.csv")
exchange <- as.data.frame(exchange)

Creating data frame

v1_updated <- c(exchange[[1]])  # Date
v2_updated <- c(exchange[[2]])  # Time
v3_updated <- c(exchange[[3]])  # Bid
v4_updated <- c(exchange[[4]])  # Ask

Giving columns correct headers

exchange_updated <- data.frame(v1_updated, v2_updated, v3_updated, v4_updated)

Calculate Daily Forex Spread

exchange_updated$Spread <- exchange_updated$Ask - exchange_updated$Bid

spread = exchange_updated$Spread

daily_spread = numeric()

daily_spread[1] = sum(spread[1:288])

for(i in 2:2463) {
  n = (i-1) * 288 + 1 
  m = i * 288          
  daily_spread[i] = sum(spread[n:m])
}

Plot daily Forex Spread

plot.ts(daily_spread, main="Forex Spread (Ask - Bid)", ylab="Spread", xlab="Time")

Calculate geometric mean function using the given formula:

\[(log(bid) + log(ask))/2\]

calculate_geometric_mean <- function(bid, ask){
  geometric_mean <- (log(bid) + log(ask))/2
  return(geometric_mean)
}

Calculating geometric mean

geometric_mean <- calculate_geometric_mean(exchange_updated$Bid, exchange_updated$Ask)

Calculate returns function that finds the difference of the consecutive logs.

calculate_daily_returns <- function(geometric_mean){
  daily_return <- numeric(length(geometric_mean) - 1)
  for (i in 2:length(geometric_mean)) {
    daily_return[i-1] <- geometric_mean[i] - geometric_mean[i-1]
  }
  return(daily_return)
}

Calculating returns and updating data frame

returns <- calculate_daily_returns(geometric_mean)

exchange_updated$Returns <- c(0, returns)

Clearing out 15 longest runs of zeros

zero_runs <- rle(exchange_updated$Returns == 0)

zero_runs_df <- data.frame(
  lengths = zero_runs$lengths,
  values = zero_runs$values,
  start_positions = cumsum(c(1, head(zero_runs$lengths, -1)))
)

longest_zero_runs <- zero_runs_df[zero_runs_df$values == TRUE, ]
longest_zero_runs <- longest_zero_runs[order(-longest_zero_runs$lengths), ]

longest_zero_runs <- head(longest_zero_runs, 15)

for (i in 1:nrow(longest_zero_runs)) {
  start <- longest_zero_runs$start_positions[i]
  end <- start + longest_zero_runs$lengths[i] - 1
  exchange_updated <- exchange_updated[-(start:end), ]
}

exchange_updated <- exchange_updated

Plot returns

plot.ts(exchange_updated$Returns*100, main="Daily Returns")

Calculating realized volatility

return_sq=(exchange_updated$Returns*100)^2

vard=0;
vard[1]=sum(return_sq[1:288])
for(i in 2:2463) {
  n=(i-1)*288; m=i*288
vard[i]=sum(return_sq[n:m])
}
variance=vard[1:2463];

realized_volatility=sqrt(variance)

Plot variance

plot.ts(variance, main="Realized Variance")

Plot Realized Volatility

plot.ts(realized_volatility, main="Realized Volatility")

Estimating \(a\) and Recovering increments functions

Estimated_MLE<-function(data,N,M, sigma)
{
  Delta_1L<- numeric(N);
  S_nM<- numeric(N);
  S_nMean<- numeric(N)
  S_nM[1]=sum(data[1:M]);
  for(n in 2:N) {
    i=(n-1)*M+1; up=n*M;
    S_nM[n] <- sum(data[floor(i):floor(up)])
  }
  S_nMean<- S_nM-mean(S_nM);
  phi_1<- (sum(S_nMean[1:N-1]*S_nMean[2:N]))/(sum(S_nMean^2));
  data=data-mean(data)
  R=length(data)
  phi_Y= (sum(data[1:R-1]*data[2:R]))/(sum(data^2))
  a_hat=-M*phi_Y+M;
  out<- a_hat;
}
Estimated_Log<-function(data, N, M){
  R = length(data);
  diff=log(data[1:R-1])-log(data[2:R]);
  a_hat=M*(max(diff));
  out<- a_hat;
}
Recovered_Increments<-function(data,N,a,M,sigma)
{
  Delta_1L<- numeric(N);
  Delta_1L[1]<-(a/(M*sigma))*sum(data[1:M])+(1/sigma-a/(2*M*sigma))*(data[M]-data[1]);
  for(n in 2:N) {
    i=(n-1)*M+1; up=n*M;
    Delta_1L[n] <-
      (a/(M*sigma))*sum(data[floor(i):floor(up)])+(1/sigma-a/(2*M*sigma))*(data[up]-data[i-1])
  }
  out<-Delta_1L;
}

CARMA_MC<-function(R,N,alpha)
{
  quantile=qnorm(1-alpha/2);
  counter_1=0;
  a_hatMLE=c();
  for(i in 1:R)
  {
    a_1L=acf(Delta_1L, plot = FALSE);
    if(abs(sqrt(N)*a_1L$acf[2])>quantile){counter_1=counter_1+1};
    a_hatMLE[i]=a_h;
  }
  freq_1=counter_1/R;
  print(c(freq_1));
  #print(a_hatMLE)
  #print(a_1L)
}

ACF plot

acf(Delta_1L,main="Recovered")

Calculating test statistic

calculate_test_statistic <- function(Delta_1L, N) {
  a_1L <- acf(Delta_1L, plot = FALSE) 
  test_stat <- abs(sqrt(N) * a_1L$acf[2])
  return(test_stat)
}
calculate_test_statistic(Delta_1L, N)
## [1] 3.761705

KS Test procedure 1

KS_test<-function(R=10,N=100,K=5000,M=100,mu=0,a=0.9,eta=1,sigma=1,alpha=0.05)
        {
        counter_2=0;
        for(i in 1:R)
                {
                Delta_1L_sample<- sample(Delta_1L, replace=T);
                mu_hat=mean(Delta_1L);
                eta_hat_sqrt=mean((Delta_1L-mu_hat)^2);
                a_1L=ks.test(Delta_1L,"pnorm", mu_hat, sqrt(eta_hat_sqrt));
                a_1L=a_1L$p.value;
                if(a_1L<0.05){counter_2=counter_2+1};
                }
        freq_2=counter_2/R;
        print(freq_2);
        print(a_1L)
}
